Male genitalia:
Endosoma with an elongate sclerotized apical region of ductus seminis wrapped with membrane; phallotheca thin, simple. Left paramere (
Figs. 100, 102
) small, U- or C-shaped, with apex somewhat spatulate. Right paramere (
Figs. 101, 103
) long, slender, slightly curving, with a slender, rounded apex that hooks behind lateral spine-like tubercle (
Figs. 129, 130
) on genital capsule 
in situ
.
